<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-l1445n4F4DSnLhtYFLu3Rg" name="Create Item definition,_Y64l4JN8EeCUs8vNyweFYw" guid="-l1445n4F4DSnLhtYFLu3Rg" changeDate="2011-08-24T03:51:41.209-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The requirements to be captured cover a number of areas such as;-&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Functional, non-functional and legal requirements, as well as the dependencies between the item and its environment.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Safety requirements that are already known about, these cover behavior achieved by similar functions, assumptions on&#xD;
    behavior expected by the item and potential consequences of behavior shortfalls, including failures modes and hazards.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task could be considered to be similar to capturing stakeholder requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The scope of item development and interfaces also needs to be understood, this is determined by considering&#xD;
    interactions with items or elements outside the scope of the system, allocation and distribution of functions to&#xD;
    architecture and operating scenarios, if they impact the functionality of the item.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This can be achieved using Use Case modeling if an MBSE approach is being used, see &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/SE%20Overview_85C27743.html&quot; guid=&quot;_NEwDka3gEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>SE&#xD;
    Overview&lt;/a>. This details a generic process for developing systems using model based techniques and gives an overview&#xD;
    of the process. The user is recommended to&amp;nbsp;examine &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Requirements%20Analysis_2F8E59B2.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_0PkdQa3gEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Elaborate System Requirements Specification&lt;/a>, in&amp;nbsp;particular,&amp;nbsp;to help with&#xD;
    the item definition.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For a more&amp;nbsp;detailed&amp;nbsp;understanding of the requirements for Item Definition the user is referred to ISO 26262&#xD;
    volume 3 clause 5.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_gBqbUJN8EeCUs8vNyweFYw" name="Determine the scope of item and relationships to other systems" guid="_gBqbUJN8EeCUs8vNyweFYw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The intent of this task is to determine the boundary of the item under development, this sets the context for its&#xD;
    interfaces and its interactions with its peer systems and their requirements,&amp;nbsp;which constrain the item under&#xD;
    development.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_ZtR2sJN9EeCUs8vNyweFYw" name="Capture the items requirements" guid="_ZtR2sJN9EeCUs8vNyweFYw">
    <sectionDescription>The items requirements come in a number of different forms, functional (behavioral), non functional (performance,&#xD;
environmental&amp;nbsp;or quality of service related) or legal (laws, national or international standards). The objective of&#xD;
this task is to capture and identify these requirements.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_v5goUJN9EeCUs8vNyweFYw" name="Capture already know safety requirements" guid="_v5goUJN9EeCUs8vNyweFYw">
    <sectionDescription>The objective of this task is to capture the behavior of the item, any assumptions on the expected behavior of the&#xD;
item&amp;nbsp;and understand the possible consequences if the behavior does not meet its expectations. This should also cover&#xD;
any know hazards and failure modes.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Provides an initial set of requirements from which the system must be developed.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
